# Documented CVE exceptions. Each entry needs a rationale + review date.
# Format: CVE-ID (one per line). Comments explain WHY it's accepted.

# --- jaegertracing/jaeger:latest (v2) ---
# Alpine 3.23.4 base ships openssl 3.5.6-r0; upstream fix in 3.5.7-r0 is
# available in alpine repos, but the maintainer has not rebuilt the image yet.
# Jaeger's HTTP surface does not expose the vulnerable TLS parsing path.
# Review after next jaegertracing/jaeger release: check https://github.com/jaegertracing/jaeger/releases
CVE-2026-45447

# Go stdlib in jaeger:latest binary is 1.26.3; fix requires 1.26.4 (or 1.25.11).
# Maintainer rebuild pending. Both CVEs are in the same stdlib bump.
CVE-2026-27145
CVE-2026-42504

# --- chrislusf/seaweedfs:latest ---
# apache/thrift v0.22.0 embedded in the Go binary. Fixed in thrift 0.23.0
# upstream. SeaweedFS uses thrift only on the internal master/volume/filer
# wire protocol, not on the S3 API surface. Waiting on chrislusf to
# release a build against thrift 0.23.0.
# Review after next SeaweedFS release: https://github.com/seaweedfs/seaweedfs/releases
CVE-2026-41602
